1
00:00:06,381 --> 00:00:09,426
<i>["Headhunt" by Okamoto's]</i>

2
00:00:09,426 --> 00:00:12,471
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:00:12,471 --> 00:00:19,520
<i>♪ ♪</i>

4
00:00:59,685 --> 00:01:02,020
‐ The reward is...
BAKYURA: 10 mil?!

5
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,981
MAN:
Let's get our 10 million yen!

6
00:01:03,981 --> 00:01:06,567
‐ Heh. Celty?
Yeah, I might know something.

7
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,652
‐ You do know something,
don't you?

8
00:01:08,652 --> 00:01:09,736
That's not fair!

9
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:10,862
SHINGEN: I hired him

10
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:12,406
to apprehend a certain woman.

11
00:01:12,406 --> 00:01:14,950
SHINRA: A woman?
‐ Think positive.

12
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:17,244
He's a monster
who wants to become human.

13
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:20,330
‐ Yah!
‐ Huh?

14
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:31,425
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:58,452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:00,412
‐ [sighs]
An arm.

17
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:02,581
An arm?
Wait, that's an arm, right?

18
00:02:02,581 --> 00:02:04,416
Ah, jeez.
It's a corpse!

19
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:08,670
Great. Now what do I do?
MAN: Get back here!

20
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:10,964
‐ You losers want
the 10 million yen that bad?

21
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:14,885
Just put away 50,000 a month
for 200 months!

22
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:18,639
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]

23
00:02:21,350 --> 00:02:23,018
MAN: What's with
the damn magic tricks?

24
00:02:23,018 --> 00:02:25,145
‐ Just look at that!

25
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:27,356
The Black Rider is driving
on the walls of the buildings!

26
00:02:27,356 --> 00:02:29,274
And the number of bikers
after the bounty

27
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:30,859
is increasing by the second.

28
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:34,529
Will we finally get to see
who the mysterious rider is?

29
00:02:34,529 --> 00:02:36,406
MAN:
Find out after this commercial‐‐

30
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:41,870
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:46,958
‐ So, uh, you guys are serious?

32
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:49,127
You're really with
the Yellow Scarves?

33
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:50,587
‐ Hey, don't sweat it.

34
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:52,339
It's not like we care
what you were doing

35
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:53,632
at the factory.

36
00:02:53,632 --> 00:02:55,300
‐ We just want to get
the 10 million yen

37
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,718
that's up for grabs,
you get what I'm saying?

38
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,637
‐ You know
where the Black Rider is,

39
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:00,639
so don't try to play us!

40
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:03,141
‐ Start off
by giving us your cell phone.

41
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:05,060
Bet you anything
it's got the Rider's number.

42
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:06,353
‐ Let go!

43
00:03:08,814 --> 00:03:09,815
‐ Huh?

44
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:14,820
Who in the hell are‐‐

45
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:15,987
‐ Damn it, you‐‐

46
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:17,656
‐ Whoa! It's Kyohei!

47
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:20,117
‐ Hurry up, and get in, guys!

48
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:28,667
[tires screeching]

49
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:31,378
‐ Damn you, bastard!
‐ Piss off.

50
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:37,008
‐ [sighs]
Thanks. That was close.

51
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,510
‐ Ah, it was nothing, really.

52
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:40,178
Sorry we were late
for hooking up with you.

53
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:42,722
‐ Hold on. You guys?
What are you doing here?

54
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,516
‐ [giggles]

55
00:03:46,309 --> 00:03:48,311
‐ Why is everyone acting crazy?

56
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:50,188
What the heck's going on?

57
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,690
‐ Well, to be honest,

58
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,900
afraid we got some bad news
for you guys.

59
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,610
We may have gotten you
out of one disaster,

60
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:57,696
but we ended dragging you
into another one.

61
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:59,406
Right now,
this area is a trouble zone,

62
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,699
like a certain Academy City

63
00:04:00,699 --> 00:04:03,076
where everyone studies
supernatural powers.

64
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,786
‐ Are you sure
you're feeling all right?

65
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:06,455
‐ There's been
a lot of stuff going down.

66
00:04:06,455 --> 00:04:08,540
No big.
‐ Stuff? What kind of stuff?

67
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,375
[Cóiste‐Bodhar neighs]
ALL: Huh?

68
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,461
‐ I should never have
taken this job.

69
00:04:12,461 --> 00:04:14,713
I haven't been thinking straight
since I lost that money.

70
00:04:14,713 --> 00:04:17,299
‐ I'd like you to hold on
to this bag.

71
00:04:17,299 --> 00:04:18,925
It'll only be for one day.

72
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:21,052
We can't have anyone finding it.

73
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:23,388
Just hang onto it
till this time tomorrow.

74
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:24,723
Then you can dump it.

75
00:04:24,723 --> 00:04:27,559
‐ Excuse me,
but who referred you to me?

76
00:04:27,559 --> 00:04:28,810
‐ An information broker.

77
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:29,978
Izaya Orihara.

78
00:04:29,978 --> 00:04:32,481
‐ Ugh. Now I get it.

79
00:04:32,481 --> 00:04:34,691
This smells really fishy.

80
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:37,194
Sorry, but I'm a transporter.

81
00:04:37,194 --> 00:04:39,946
If you need a safe‐deposit box,
try a bank.

82
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:42,574
‐ Maybe this'll
change your mind.

83
00:04:42,574 --> 00:04:45,076
[cash register cha‐chings]

84
00:04:45,076 --> 00:04:46,870
‐ I'd be happy to do it!

85
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:47,829
[men yelling]

86
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:49,498
What do I do if the police come?

87
00:04:49,498 --> 00:04:51,291
Whatever. I don't care.

88
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:54,711
I just don't want Shinra and I
to live apart... Shinra...

89
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:56,755
[Cóiste‐Bodhar whickers]
No. This isn't good.

90
00:04:56,755 --> 00:04:58,006
Get a hold of yourself!

91
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:00,509
You can do this!
Get a hold of yourself!

92
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:02,677
It's gonna work out! Huh?

93
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:03,637
That's...

94
00:05:03,637 --> 00:05:05,597
‐ The Black Rider?

95
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:13,438
‐ Celty!
‐ It is Celty!

96
00:05:13,438 --> 00:05:15,232
‐ Hey, now Celty's here!
‐ What's going on here, Mikado?

97
00:05:15,232 --> 00:05:17,859
‐ [gasps] Look!
It's the Black Rider, Kururi!

98
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:19,277
The Black Rider!
‐ Okay.

99
00:05:21,613 --> 00:05:24,449
CELTY: Sorry.
Bikers are chasing me. Run!

100
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:25,951
‐ Hate to tell you this‐‐

101
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:27,786
afraid we're the ones
who stirred 'em up.

102
00:05:27,786 --> 00:05:31,706
[men yelling]

103
00:05:31,706 --> 00:05:33,124
‐ Gah!

104
00:05:33,124 --> 00:05:35,961
‐ We do have one thing
in our favor.

105
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:37,587
None of those bikers are locals,

106
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:40,757
while most of us here in the van
are members of the Dollars.

107
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:42,133
They want to mess around
on our turf,

108
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,970
we have every right
to kick their asses.

109
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:45,971
Punch it.

110
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:47,764
‐ You bet.

111
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:49,349
[men yelling]

112
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:50,809
‐ [gasps]
What do we do now?

113
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:52,477
Think we should call the police?

114
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:54,396
‐ I'm sure that someone's
already called 'em.

115
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:55,939
Don't sweat it.

116
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:58,066
I'll see that nothing happens
to you high schoolers.

117
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:00,735
‐ Right.

118
00:06:03,572 --> 00:06:06,116
‐ Are you feeling all right,
Mikado?

119
00:06:06,116 --> 00:06:08,660
‐ Y‐yeah. It's all good.

120
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:10,829
Sorry.
Wish they could let you two off.

121
00:06:10,829 --> 00:06:12,789
‐ That's not what I‐‐
forget it.

122
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,291
It's no big deal.

123
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:17,627
CELTY: So many things
have happened in this past year.

124
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:21,089
I met Mikado and the others,
joined the Dollars,

125
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,716
became friends with Anri,

126
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:26,094
and most importantly, Shinra.

127
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:28,930
‐ What? Yuma,
your definition of <i>tsundere</i>

128
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,348
is way too narrow, like toast.

129
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:31,933
‐ Celty doesn't
fit the mold,

130
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,894
since she's honest
but can't be totally cold.

131
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:35,687
She's more of
a big sister type character

132
00:06:35,687 --> 00:06:37,814
who'd take care of others
in the good old days.

133
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:39,733
Like the one
who lets herself be coddled

134
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:41,943
by an unreliable big brother.

135
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:43,403
Right! She's a big‐‐

136
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:45,739
‐ Shinra, since those guys
came into our home,

137
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:47,449
they haven't stopped
talking about me.

138
00:06:47,449 --> 00:06:48,700
What's up with that?

139
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,368
‐ Yeah,
I suppose you're gonna find out,

140
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:51,620
so I might as well tell you.

141
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:53,496
I ran into them at a bar
earlier,

142
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:56,041
and they were all talking about
how amazing you are,

143
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:57,542
and things kind of slipped out.

144
00:06:57,542 --> 00:06:59,669
I had to brag
that you were my girlfriend

145
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:01,296
and gush over this and that,

146
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:02,964
like
everything we did on our dates

147
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:04,174
and some other details.

148
00:07:04,174 --> 00:07:06,926
Yeah, alcohol's a scary thing.

149
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:08,470
Stop it.
Ow. Ow. Ow.

150
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:09,679
What are you doing, Celty?

151
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,431
Maybe you really are <i>tsundere.</i>

152
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:13,058
Ow. Ow. Ow. Ow. Ow!

153
00:07:13,058 --> 00:07:16,561
CELTY:
The truth is, I was so happy.

154
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:18,897
I've been jumping for joy
this year.

155
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:20,023
Almost too happy.

156
00:07:20,023 --> 00:07:21,858
Considering all that,

157
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:25,737
well, I can't just‐‐
I can't just give it up now!

158
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:29,282
‐ Serious?
Gotcha.

159
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:31,701
You know, considering
everything we've been through,

160
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:33,745
we've never really been
formally introduced,

161
00:07:33,745 --> 00:07:36,539
so I hope you won't think I'm
out of line here, but listen.

162
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:39,459
I want a chance to pay you back,
Celty, okay?

163
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:42,087
[horn sounding]
Hmm?

164
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:46,966
[men yelling]

165
00:07:49,594 --> 00:07:50,595
‐ Hmm?

166
00:07:51,763 --> 00:07:53,598
[grunting and yelling]

167
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:58,019
[men yelling]

168
00:08:05,652 --> 00:08:12,283
<i>♪ ♪</i>

169
00:08:14,244 --> 00:08:17,288
[horns sounding]

170
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:22,585
[men yelling]

171
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,302
‐ All right.
Get out, and make a run for it.

172
00:08:31,302 --> 00:08:32,470
ALL: Huh?

173
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:34,889
‐ Okay,
but what are you gonna do?

174
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:36,141
‐ Well, the way I see it,

175
00:08:36,141 --> 00:08:38,059
Celty's a lady.

176
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:40,103
At least she looks like one,
anyway.

177
00:08:40,103 --> 00:08:41,646
Wouldn't you agree, Saburo?

178
00:08:41,646 --> 00:08:43,231
‐ Huh? Yeah, sure.

179
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:44,983
‐ We couldn't call ourselves
gentlemen

180
00:08:44,983 --> 00:08:48,361
if we left a lady at the mercy
of those thugs, right?

181
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:50,822
‐ Right.

182
00:08:50,822 --> 00:08:52,490
[tires screeching]

183
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:55,869
‐ Hey, Aoba, take care of Anri
and those two girls.

184
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:58,621
‐ What? Mikado, wait!

185
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:00,165
Where did Anri go?

186
00:09:00,165 --> 00:09:02,000
‐ What now?
‐ [sighs]

187
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,543
Guess
we'll have to wait and see.

188
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,128
Who knows
what's gonna happen next?

189
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:07,672
But can you believe
we got such a close‐up look?

190
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:09,674
I mean, think about it‐‐
wouldn't it be cool

191
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:11,760
if we actually
got to meet Celty?

192
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,470
‐ What the hell?

193
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:15,388
[men grunt]

194
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:20,310
‐ Damn it.

195
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:22,020
They're coming back?

196
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:24,856
I told them to run. Huh?

197
00:09:24,856 --> 00:09:26,316
‐ You can leave them all to me.

198
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:28,068
You should make your escape.

199
00:09:34,157 --> 00:09:35,700
CELTY: Mikado!

200
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,160
Anri!

201
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:39,204
[man grunting]

202
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:42,499
Who's that?

203
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:43,792
Wait.

204
00:09:43,792 --> 00:09:44,834
I know that aura.

205
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:46,086
It's...

206
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:50,465
This morning's client.

207
00:09:50,465 --> 00:09:52,842
‐ Please let me pay you back
for your services.

208
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:05,730
‐ Holy crap.
What the hell's going on?

209
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:08,108
‐ Hurry.
Please go look after Mother.

210
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:10,235
‐ Mother?

211
00:10:10,235 --> 00:10:12,445
Saika.

212
00:10:16,241 --> 00:10:18,368
I'll leave things to you
if you insist.

213
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:21,788
My friends are‐‐
no, I'm in danger.

214
00:10:21,788 --> 00:10:24,415
I'll give you two pieces
of advice to thank you.

215
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:27,293
First, run from any motorcycle
officers you see.

216
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:29,921
There's a monster
in their ranks!

217
00:10:29,921 --> 00:10:31,965
Secondly,
don't ever pick a fight

218
00:10:31,965 --> 00:10:33,842
with anyone dressed
as a bartender.

219
00:10:33,842 --> 00:10:35,969
No matter what.

220
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:39,097
SHIZUO:
Bunch of damn petty thieves!

221
00:10:39,097 --> 00:10:40,890
BOTH: Huh?

222
00:10:46,396 --> 00:10:47,856
‐ Ah!

223
00:10:56,823 --> 00:11:00,118
‐ Damn it. We can't go home
after taking that beatdown.

224
00:11:00,118 --> 00:11:02,036
The boss'll kill us
when he hears about this.

225
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:03,872
‐ We got to at least flex
a little muscle

226
00:11:03,872 --> 00:11:06,416
and put the fear of God
into the local gang, right?

227
00:11:06,416 --> 00:11:09,627
‐ Hey, Rasta Boy,
I got a question for you.

228
00:11:09,627 --> 00:11:11,504
What's the name
of the baddest gang around here,

229
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:13,256
and where can we find 'em?

230
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:15,633
‐ Are you guys trying to pick
a fight with 'em or something?

231
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:18,887
‐ What do you think?
‐ Toramaru from Saitama, right?

232
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:20,805
Your gang's boss
is a ladies' man,

233
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:23,183
but I've also heard that
he doesn't put up with any crap.

234
00:11:23,183 --> 00:11:25,768
He's not gonna be down
with what you guys are planning.

235
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:27,103
‐ Why don't you
shut the hell up,

236
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:29,314
you dreadlocked piece of‐‐

237
00:11:32,025 --> 00:11:34,068
‐ What the hell, man?

238
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:35,820
My shirt.

239
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:38,281
My little brother gave
this shirt to me.

240
00:11:38,281 --> 00:11:40,742
You guys are dead!

241
00:11:40,742 --> 00:11:42,619
[men yelling]

242
00:11:53,922 --> 00:11:56,132
‐ It's tranquil today
in the city.

243
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:59,010
Oh. There was some news
on that reward for Celty.

244
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:02,138
It's been cancelled
after a police reprimand.

245
00:12:02,138 --> 00:12:04,515
Still,
I hear that CEO's in a good mood

246
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:07,602
since they got
Ruri Hijiribe's contract.

247
00:12:07,602 --> 00:12:08,853
‐ Why, it's fabulous!

248
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,521
How about a round of applause,
people?

249
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:11,439
Celebrate!

250
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:12,899
This is a happy occasion,

251
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:14,609
one I've got no problem
accepting,

252
00:12:14,609 --> 00:12:15,902
even with this scandal,

253
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:17,153
which is why I'm giving you two

254
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:19,155
my blessing here and now.

255
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,865
[laughing]

256
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:22,825
IZAYA: Her old agency
has been shut down,

257
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:27,830
since it seems their CEO,
Yodogiri, has gone missing.

258
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:31,125
‐ Well, the rest is up
to our young couple over here.

259
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:34,093
Us old fogies can go home.

260
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:39,592
‐ The events that led up
to Hollywood discovering

261
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:41,302
she had powers,

262
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:44,305
the reason
that she became a serial killer,

263
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:46,057
what happened back then,

264
00:12:46,057 --> 00:12:48,476
and what Yodogiri did to me‐‐

265
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:50,979
I haven't told you
any of that yet.

266
00:12:50,979 --> 00:12:52,397
‐ If you don't want to say,

267
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:54,232
then you shouldn't
force yourself.

268
00:12:54,232 --> 00:12:56,818
‐ To tell the truth,
I would like you to hear it.

269
00:12:56,818 --> 00:12:58,236
‐ No, thanks.

270
00:12:58,236 --> 00:13:00,280
I'm sure that once you tell me,
that's it.

271
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,739
You'll end it all.

272
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:06,119
Everyone can clearly see
how I am.

273
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:08,121
Since I can't share
people's feelings,

274
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:09,914
I thought that I should
at least try my best

275
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:11,249
to understand them,

276
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:13,751
so I've been observing people
closely.

277
00:13:13,751 --> 00:13:17,130
That's why I have a pretty good
idea of what you're thinking.

278
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:19,257
I'd prefer it
if you didn't die, Ruri,

279
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:21,968
so I don't want you
to tell me anything.

280
00:13:21,968 --> 00:13:23,428
‐ You know something?

281
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:27,307
I think you might be
some kind of monster after all.

282
00:13:27,307 --> 00:13:30,101
But hear me out,
because ever since I was young,

283
00:13:30,101 --> 00:13:32,520
I felt the need
to destroy everything I touched,

284
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:35,356
and yet, the fear of losing
those closest to me

285
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:36,774
outweighed that need.

286
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:39,068
I couldn't become a monster
completely

287
00:13:39,068 --> 00:13:40,945
unless I destroyed myself,

288
00:13:40,945 --> 00:13:43,740
but in the end, I think
the thought of losing myself

289
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:46,242
was the one thing
I was most frightened of.

290
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,952
‐ The fear of losing something.

291
00:13:47,952 --> 00:13:49,829
Sounds to me
like you might consider that

292
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:52,582
another kind of love.

293
00:13:52,582 --> 00:13:55,001
There's something
that I never told you.

294
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:56,544
‐ And what's that?

295
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:58,171
‐ When you pushed me down
on the bed

296
00:13:58,171 --> 00:14:00,298
and got on top of me, I think

297
00:14:00,298 --> 00:14:02,258
that moment got me
extremely flustered.

298
00:14:02,258 --> 00:14:03,468
‐ Huh?

299
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:05,887
‐ My heart started beating
very quickly,

300
00:14:05,887 --> 00:14:08,431
and my chest felt hot.

301
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:10,641
‐ Is that your way
of winning me over?

302
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,102
‐ I was only explaining
the facts.

303
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:17,982
‐ Well, that side of you‐‐
it's kind of charming.

304
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:22,070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

305
00:14:22,070 --> 00:14:23,863
‐ After purchasing
all these clothes,

306
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,656
you're still not done shopping?

307
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:26,991
‐ Not quite yet.

308
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:28,826
‐ You're in no position
to complain, Egor.

309
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:30,995
We put up the money
to pay your entire medical bill,

310
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:33,831
and you ended up letting
Celty get away just like that.

311
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:35,750
IZAYA:
The twins were on a mission.

312
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,753
They wanted to meet Celty
no matter what.

313
00:14:38,753 --> 00:14:40,671
They got some information
from a certain source

314
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:41,964
that the envelope was addressed

315
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,800
to a transporter
on a black bike.

316
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,177
In return
for paying the medical bills,

317
00:14:46,177 --> 00:14:50,181
they asked Russia Sushi for help
in putting on a little show.

318
00:14:50,181 --> 00:14:53,810
The head chef was to contact
Celty while in disguise.

319
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:57,063
Egor was to hide inside a bag
that Celty would transport

320
00:14:57,063 --> 00:14:58,564
and,
once he reached her hideout,

321
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:00,858
contact my sisters
via cell phone.

322
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:03,027
At least, that was the plan.

323
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:06,364
Naturally, a scheme like that
would never work out.

324
00:15:06,364 --> 00:15:09,534
But the 1 million yen
they found on the street

325
00:15:09,534 --> 00:15:11,619
ultimately did make its way
back to Celty,

326
00:15:11,619 --> 00:15:13,329
so I guess you could say

327
00:15:13,329 --> 00:15:15,039
those two actually did
a rare good deed.

328
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,208
‐ Hey, Egor,
you were the one who ended up

329
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:18,751
beating the snot out
of those bikers

330
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:20,586
at the underpass, weren't you?

331
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,463
I knew
you had to be someone special,

332
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,423
but you've got to be
a Russian super soldier

333
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:25,716
to pull off something like that.

334
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:27,051
‐ You're amazing.

335
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:30,263
‐ No. That other person deserves
the credit.

336
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,392
IZAYA: In reality,
Egor's known to be

337
00:15:34,392 --> 00:15:37,228
the seventh most feared hit man
in Russia.

338
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:40,815
Also known as the
"Philosophical Killing Machine."

339
00:15:40,815 --> 00:15:42,984
Well,
if anything did happen with him,

340
00:15:42,984 --> 00:15:45,236
it would be their problem,
not mine.

341
00:15:45,236 --> 00:15:47,905
Now, as for what's going on
with Celty...

342
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:49,073
‐ All right, guys.

343
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:50,616
Make sure you pay attention,
now.

344
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,243
For sagohachi‐style pickles,

345
00:15:52,243 --> 00:15:54,745
the quality of the malted rice
and the ratio you use

346
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:56,581
is what makes or breaks
this dish.

347
00:15:56,581 --> 00:15:58,666
So we start off
with this bed of sagohachi

348
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,960
that I brought from home,
and it's fully fermented.

349
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:04,046
‐ I'm home. Hey,
what the heck's going on here?

350
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,673
‐ Since I'm between jobs now,

351
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:07,925
I thought it'd be a good time
to learn how to cook.

352
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:10,469
I went to ask Anri
for lessons first,

353
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:13,055
but it seems
she's not a very good cook.

354
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,600
Then I tried
to get Erika to teach me,

355
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:18,269
but Japanese cuisine
wasn't her thing.

356
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:21,105
This is who Anri brought over.

357
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:26,944
<i>♪ ♪</i>

358
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:29,530
ALL: [gasp]
‐ She can really cook, huh?

359
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:31,449
‐ I think most would say
she's top‐notch,

360
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:33,743
which means she's
super top‐notch in my book.

361
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:36,037
‐ You're such a flatterer,
aren't you?

362
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:39,040
Okay. Now you just lay them
in the bed of sagohachi

363
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,209
and let them pickle all night.

364
00:16:41,209 --> 00:16:42,460
‐ All night?

365
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:44,795
‐ Yep. All night.
‐ No shortcuts?

366
00:16:44,795 --> 00:16:46,339
‐ No shortcuts.

367
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:48,925
‐ What now?
We've got nothing for dinner.

368
00:16:48,925 --> 00:16:51,385
‐ Hmm.

369
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:53,763
Hot pot!
CELTY: Hot pot?

370
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:56,140
‐ Yeah, and while we're at it,
let's invite all our friends!

371
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:58,142
We're going to have ourselves
a hot pot party.

372
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,523
[all voicing agreement]

373
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:06,776
‐ Open wide!

374
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,737
So good!

375
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:11,322
[giggling]

376
00:17:11,322 --> 00:17:12,782
‐ Mm‐hmm.

377
00:17:15,576 --> 00:17:17,161
‐ Shouldn't you eat?

378
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:18,537
‐ Well, it's like this.

379
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:20,289
Just seeing
the smile on your face

380
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:21,791
is enough to keep me going.

381
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:23,876
‐ That's a bit much.

382
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:26,128
But thanks.

383
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:28,673
‐ Oh, man. These last few days
have been pretty tough,

384
00:17:28,673 --> 00:17:29,840
haven't they?

385
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,509
‐ Yeah.

386
00:17:31,509 --> 00:17:33,261
It makes me wonder
if I'm really doing

387
00:17:33,261 --> 00:17:34,345
the right thing.

388
00:17:34,345 --> 00:17:36,430
‐ How so?

389
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:39,183
‐ I'm just trying to figure out
if being a transporter

390
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:40,476
is the best job for me.

391
00:17:40,476 --> 00:17:43,354
‐ And what brought this up
all of a sudden?

392
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:45,731
‐ It's just, whenever
I take on a dangerous job,

393
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:50,695
even if I'm okay with the risk,
it causes trouble for you, and‐‐

394
00:17:50,695 --> 00:17:52,363
‐ We're family, Celty.

395
00:17:52,363 --> 00:17:54,657
A little trouble means nothing.

396
00:17:54,657 --> 00:17:56,659
And as long as I've got
you by my side,

397
00:17:56,659 --> 00:17:59,537
whatever comes, it'll never
feel like trouble to me.

398
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:01,080
‐ Shinra...

399
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,540
‐ And besides,

400
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:04,875
I overcame
the greatest obstacle of all‐‐

401
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,627
winning your love.

402
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:09,046
Oh.
[chuckles]

403
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:13,384
TARO: By the way,
I was at a hot pot party

404
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:14,635
with my friends today.

405
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:17,013
SETTON: What a coincidence.
So was I.

406
00:18:17,013 --> 00:18:19,724
KANRA: What? Hot pot?
At this time of year?

407
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:21,183
KYO: Oh, what a coincidence.

408
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:23,352
We were enjoying
some shabu‐shabu ourselves

409
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:25,021
a little earlier today.

410
00:18:25,021 --> 00:18:26,564
SAN: It was good.

411
00:18:26,564 --> 00:18:28,899
IZAYA: Kururi, Mairu‐‐
I know it's you.

412
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:30,860
How did you find this address?

413
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:32,361
KURURI:
Ms. Namie was kind enough

414
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:34,322
to point us
in the right direction.

415
00:18:34,322 --> 00:18:36,991
Other brother.

416
00:18:36,991 --> 00:18:38,576
IZAYA/MAIRU:
Do you even have friends

417
00:18:38,576 --> 00:18:39,827
who will join you for hot pot?

418
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:42,246
‐ He asks.
‐ How mean.

419
00:18:44,999 --> 00:18:46,417
KURURI:
I'd greatly appreciate it

420
00:18:46,417 --> 00:18:47,585
if you wouldn't intrude

421
00:18:47,585 --> 00:18:49,295
into the friendships
of young ladies,

422
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:50,379
brother, dear.

423
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:51,881
KURURI/IZAYA: It's a secret.

424
00:18:51,881 --> 00:18:53,591
IZAYA: Hmm? Use privacy mode.

425
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:55,593
Better yet, get out of here,
you two.

426
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:58,512
BAKYURA: I went to have sukiyaki
with a female friend of mine.

427
00:18:58,512 --> 00:18:59,889
Just the two of us.

428
00:18:59,889 --> 00:19:01,432
You heard of these places?

429
00:19:01,432 --> 00:19:04,894
All‐you‐can‐eat sukiyaki joints
that charge around 1,500 yen?

430
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:07,480
TARO: Oh, yeah.
There's a whole chain of 'em.

431
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:10,232
SAIKA:
I had hot pot with Setton.

432
00:19:10,232 --> 00:19:11,609
It was delicious.

433
00:19:11,609 --> 00:19:12,735
KANRA: I swear!

434
00:19:12,735 --> 00:19:14,779
You guys have no sense
of the seasons.

435
00:19:14,779 --> 00:19:16,906
You're only supposed to eat
hot pot style dishes

436
00:19:16,906 --> 00:19:18,783
in the winter!

437
00:19:18,783 --> 00:19:21,285
‐ Do you have any plans?
‐ For what?

438
00:19:21,285 --> 00:19:23,245
‐ Thought I'd treat you
to some hot pot.

439
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:25,081
Shabu‐shabu, or maybe some crab.

440
00:19:25,081 --> 00:19:26,999
You can choose
whatever you want.

441
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,835
‐ Because your little chat room
friends are having hot pot?

442
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:32,463
If you're looking for someone
to soothe your injured vanity,

443
00:19:32,463 --> 00:19:33,964
you should try a therapist.

444
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:36,717
‐ Hmm?
You read that?

445
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:39,720
Namie, it wasn't you
who happened to tell my sisters

446
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,263
about Celty, now, was it?

447
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:43,766
‐ Who knows?
I couldn't really say.

448
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:46,102
‐ [laughs]
You've turned into a force

449
00:19:46,102 --> 00:19:48,479
to be reckoned with,
haven't you?

450
00:19:48,479 --> 00:19:49,980
‐ Still,
I've discovered one thing.

451
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,482
‐ And that is?

452
00:19:51,482 --> 00:19:54,193
‐ That life goes on,
even without your involvement.

453
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:56,404
And no one invited you
to have hot pot,

454
00:19:56,404 --> 00:19:58,864
so I guess you aren't
the center of the universe.

455
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,325
‐ [laughs]

456
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:02,993
All I did
was make an observation

457
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:05,162
of how some others
spent their day off.

458
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:06,414
But I think it's about time

459
00:20:06,414 --> 00:20:08,833
I start enjoying
my own days off.

460
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:12,253
After all, there are
potential sparks everywhere.

461
00:20:12,253 --> 00:20:14,964
ANRI: I didn't realize.

462
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:19,468
‐ Forgive the intrusion,
my lovely young lady.

463
00:20:19,468 --> 00:20:23,472
‐ To think
Saika would act on its own.

464
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:25,891
If...if Saika had stabbed

465
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:28,394
Mikado and Masaomi
the same way‐‐

466
00:20:28,394 --> 00:20:30,813
SAIKA: I love you...
I love you...

467
00:20:30,813 --> 00:20:34,275
I love you...I love you...
I love you...

468
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:38,028
‐ Nothing? Still haven't had
any luck finding Yodogiri?

469
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:39,613
‐ Looks like
the other organizations

470
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:41,866
are starting to think
we offed him ourselves.

471
00:20:41,866 --> 00:20:43,409
‐ That sly old dog.

472
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:46,454
I can't believe he joined forces
with multiple groups.

473
00:20:46,454 --> 00:20:48,372
‐ We can't let our guard down.

474
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:49,874
‐ This guy's way too sketchy.

475
00:20:49,874 --> 00:20:51,709
I don't believe for a minute
this bullshit

476
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:53,753
about being a talent agency CEO.

477
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:55,671
‐ We got to get
the goods on this guy.

478
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:57,673
No matter what it costs,
we're gonna make sure

479
00:20:57,673 --> 00:20:59,884
we bury that con artist dead.

480
00:20:59,884 --> 00:21:01,552
‐ That Mikado.

481
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:03,804
He's interesting,
that's for sure.

482
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,556
No doubt about that.

483
00:21:05,556 --> 00:21:06,724
I told you about that time

484
00:21:06,724 --> 00:21:09,226
the bikers were after him,
right?

485
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:11,771
I mean, the situation
was just dripping with danger.

486
00:21:11,771 --> 00:21:13,939
Anyone else
would've broke down and cried.

487
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:18,027
But he didn't flinch.

488
00:21:18,027 --> 00:21:19,236
Even with all that pressure.

489
00:21:19,236 --> 00:21:20,905
He loves
those surreal situations,

490
00:21:20,905 --> 00:21:23,574
like stuff
straight out of some comic book.

491
00:21:23,574 --> 00:21:24,700
It's almost unbelievable.

492
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,744
He thrives on it,

493
00:21:26,744 --> 00:21:28,996
and that's exactly
the kind of guy he is.

494
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:30,289
See what I mean?

495
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,082
That's why
Mikado started the Dollars

496
00:21:32,082 --> 00:21:33,083
in the first place.

497
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:34,418
‐ I'm not sure I get it.

498
00:21:34,418 --> 00:21:35,461
‐ Sounds like
Mikado's just trying

499
00:21:35,461 --> 00:21:36,504
to keep from getting bored.

500
00:21:36,504 --> 00:21:38,005
‐ Things got interesting

501
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:39,673
when the feud between
the Yellow Scarves and Dollars

502
00:21:39,673 --> 00:21:41,300
was heating up.

503
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:45,054
It'd be lame if it ended without
much damage to either gang.

