‐ So,
you want to make a new spark

505
00:21:46,597 --> 00:21:47,932
and have 'em start a fight, huh?

506
00:21:47,932 --> 00:21:50,434
‐ Yeah, but even if we did,

507
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:51,977
there's someone
catching those sparks

508
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:53,896
and using them
for his own reasons.

509
00:21:53,896 --> 00:21:56,440
Got to deal with that hyena
first.

510
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:58,526
Izaya Orihara has got to go.

511
00:21:58,526 --> 00:22:00,236
Oh, but not the twins.

512
00:22:00,236 --> 00:22:03,447
Nobody lays a hands
on Izaya's sisters, okay?

513
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:04,824
I got a thing for those two.

514
00:22:04,824 --> 00:22:06,492
They kind of kissed me
out of the blue,

515
00:22:06,492 --> 00:22:08,118
know what I mean?

516
00:22:08,118 --> 00:22:10,287
‐ Oh, give me a break, Izumi.

517
00:22:10,287 --> 00:22:12,248
‐ Never use my old name.

518
00:22:12,248 --> 00:22:14,291
It reminds me
of my scumbag brother.

519
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:17,586
IZAYA: What I'm trying to do
is gather those sparks

520
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:19,505
and toss them all in one place,

521
00:22:19,505 --> 00:22:22,466
and then
I'm going to say to them,

522
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:24,385
"Your vacation's over.

523
00:22:24,385 --> 00:22:26,136
You piece of shit."

524
00:22:26,136 --> 00:22:28,973
[man singing in Japanese]

525
00:23:58,020 --> 00:23:59,313
NAMIE: It's so asinine.

526
00:23:59,313 --> 00:24:00,397
I wonder why the world

527
00:24:00,397 --> 00:24:02,316
is teeming with such fools.

528
00:24:02,316 --> 00:24:04,568
Who needs him?
Or him? Or him?

529
00:24:04,568 --> 00:24:06,570
All I need is my Seiji.

530
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,614
Still...next time‐‐

531
00:24:08,614 --> 00:24:10,824
"No One Knows
What the Future Holds."

